## Group Products

Resources related to Product in the API.

## Products [/products]

Products endpoint allows you to list the individual (i.e.) non-bundle product information. objective of this endpoint is to return all the applicable levels of excess, payment methods, annual service visit eligibility and supported appliance types of a product. Responses from this endpoint will be retuned in JSON format only. Features will side-loaded to describe the parameters of a product which form a feature.

#### Product
Product as a resource represents following information:

| Property | Type | As request | As response | Description |
| :-------------------- | :---------- | :----------| :---------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| id | string | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | Product code is considered as the unique identifier. |
| description | string | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | Product description is considered as the unique identifier. |
| type | string | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | Indicates the product type like `Services`. |
| annualServiceApplicable | boolean | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` |  Indicates the product's annual service visit eligibility. |
| excesses | Array of int | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | All applicable levels of excess. |
| paymentMethods | Array of string | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | All applicable payment methods. |
| appliances | Array of string | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | All applicable appliances. |
| annualServiceMandatory | Boolean | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | Indicates whether ASV is mandatory. |
| productFeature | string | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | Indicates the base/default feature of the product. |

### Retrieve a specific product [GET /products/{id}]

+ Parameters

    + id (required, string) - Id of the product

+ Request

    + Headers

            cid: 05e230bf-a9cf-4b31-bc54-d3a995f62526

